OL,3,C'I feel loved': Irish politician's
OL,4,CCork accent makes him a star in Jamaica
OL,6,F"The majority of Irish people who went
OL,7,Fto Jamaica came from Cork and Monster.
OL,8,FThey would have been indentured
OL,9,Fservants brought to the Caribbean, a
OL,10,Ftype of slavery, but it was only
OL,11,Fshort," he told Jamaica Observer.
OL,13,F"They were treated horrendously but
OL,14,Fnot as bad as slaves who were taken
OL,15,Ffrom Africa," he added.
OL,17,FMany of these people would be
OL,18,Findentured servants, who were forcibly
OL,19,Fdeported soon after the island was
OL,20,Fseized by the British during Oliver
OL,21,FCromwell's protectorate in the 1650s.
